data.enText: a record of the number or amount of sth, especially one that you can keep adding to

data.chText: 他希望提高在过去九场比赛中打进三球的纪录。
data.enText: He hopes to improve on his tally of three goals in the past nine games.

data.chText: 在外出期间，把你的花费都记录下来。
data.enText: Keep a tally of how much you spend while you're away.

data.chText: （说法、数字等）与…符合（或一致）；吻合
data.enText: to be the same as or to match another person's account of sth, another set of figures, etc.

data.chText: 她对于事情的叙述和另一个证人的说法完全吻合。
data.enText: Her report of what happened tallied exactly with the story of another witness.

data.chText: 计算（总的数目、成本等）；合计
data.enText: to calculate the total number, cost, etc. of sth

ex.chText: 比赛离终场还有两分钟时，双方比分为5比0。
ex.enText: The score was five-nil with two minutes left in the game.

ex.chText: 他阅读测验的成绩很令人失望。
ex.enText: His score on the reading test was very disappointing.
The boy had an IQ score of 126.

synonyms.bx: 指运动、比赛、考试、科学测验等的得分。

ex.chText: 他英语得了一个Ａ，老师感到很惊讶。
ex.enText: The teacher was surprised that he got a grade A in English.

ex.chText: 她努力学习，取得了好成绩。
ex.enText: She worked hard and got good grades.

synonyms.bx: 指学习或考试成绩，通常用字母而非数字表示。

ex.enText: My mark in chemistry is B.

ex.chText: 她这学期的成绩略有提高。
ex.enText: Her marks have been a bit higher this term.
He got full marks on the final examination.

synonyms.bx: 尤指老师给学生的分数、成绩。

ex.enText: He is two points behind the leader.

ex.chText: 如果你不能准时完成字谜就扣1分。
ex.enText: You lose a point if you can't complete the puzzle on time.
He got 95 points in the English test.

synonyms.bx: 主要指运动、比赛中的得分，有时也指考试的分数。

ex.chText: 你知道你的考试成绩吗？
ex.enText: Do you know your exam results?

ex.chText: 足球比赛的结果将在午夜公布。
ex.enText: The football results will be announced at midnight.

synonyms.bx: 指比赛的最终结果，或某一门考试的得分。

ex.chText: 她在今天的比赛中获得了创纪录的比分。
ex.enText: She made a record tally at today's game.

ex.chText: 目前英格兰队的积分是9分，苏格兰队是7分。
ex.enText: England's tally at the moment is 9 points, against Scotland's 7.

synonyms.bx: 指比赛等活动中到某一时间段的得分或积分。

tr: a score in baseball made by a runner touching all four bases safely
example: the Yankees scored 3 runs in the bottom of the 9th
their first tally came in the 3rd inning
the counting continued for several hours

tr: a bill for an amount due

example: Add all the people in this town to those of the neighboring town
The home team scored many times
He hit .300 in the past season
The two stories don't agree in many details
The handwriting checks with the signature on the check
The suspect's fingerprints don't match those on the gun

value.def: A tally is a record of amounts or numbers which you keep changing and adding to as the activity which affects it progresses.

example.ex: They do not keep a tally of visitors to the palace, but it is very popular...
example.tran: 他们没有对参观宫殿的人数进行统计，不过这地方很受欢迎。

example.ex: The final tally was 817 votes for her and 731 for Mr Lee.
example.tran: 最后得出的票数是她 817 票，李先生 731 票。

value.def: If one number or statement tallies with another, they agree with each other or are exactly the same. You can also say that two numbers or statements tally .

example.ex: Its own estimate of three hundred tallies with that of another survey...
example.tran: 其估计数目 300 与另一项调查的结果相吻合。

example.ex: This description didn't seem to tally with what we saw...
example.tran: 这一描述似乎与我们目睹的情况不符。

example.ex: The figures didn't seem to tally.

value.def: If you tally numbers, items, or totals, you count them.

example.ex: ...as we tally the number of workers who have been laid off this year...
example.tran: 我们统计今年下岗工人数量的时候

example.ex: When the final numbers are tallied, sales will almost certainly have fallen.
example.tran: 等到最终的数字统计出来后，几乎可以肯定销售额下降了。

example.ex: Bookkeepers haven't yet tallied up the total cost.
example.tran: 会计还没有计算出总成本。
